commit.message:
Introduce full org-fold support (#48)

* Add support for org-fold link toggling

* Change the implementation of the just-brackets option

When `org-appear-autolinks' is set to `just-brackets', manually adjust
start and end in `org-appear--show-invisible' instead of entering a
separate condition clause. Simplifies the code that now has to check for the
`org-fold' feature.

Fix README

Toggle just brackets around links (#44)

* Allow autolinks to show just brackets

This commit allows org-appear-autolinks to be set to 'just-brackets,
which instructs org-appear to show just a pair of brackets around a
link under point, and no more.  URLs can still be viewed and edited
using `org-insert-link' if needed.

commit.message:
Finalise the implementation of the only-on-change feature (#35)

* Provide a custom variable to control toggling

Add the `org-appear-trigger' custom variable that controls the mode
of operation. When set to `on-change', toggle elements only when
the buffer is modified or on mouse click. When set to `always', always
toggle elements.

* Keep track of toggling

With the new `on-change' operation mode, we have to remember
if an element has been toggled previously to keep updating it
even if the user does not make new changes to the buffer.

commit.message:
Make sub/superscripts toggling consistent with Org (#31)

Org ignores sub/superscripts without curly braces when
`org-use-sub-superscripts' is not set to t. Do not toggle
the ignored sub/superscripts in this case.
